An open space before the Royal Palace (once that of Œdipus) at Thebes.
The back-scene represents the front of the palace, with three doors, of which the central is the largest, being the principal entrance to the court of the house.
At daybreak, on the morning after the fall of the two brothers and the flight of the Argives.
ANTIGONE calls ISMENE forth from the house, In order to speak with her apart.
